'''Christopher Warren Morris''' (born June 7, 1949)<ref name=OCLCinfo>{{cite web|title=Christopher W. Morris|url=http://errol.oclc.org/laf/n90-654558.html|publisher=Online Computer Library Center, Inc. (OCLC)|accessdate=16 April 2014}}</ref> is professor and chair of [[philosophy]] at the [[University of Maryland]], where he is also a member of the Faculty of Politics, Philosophy, and Public Policy.<ref name=CV>{{cite web|title=Department of Philosophy - Christopher W. Morris, Professor & Chair (CV)|url=http://www.philosophy.umd.edu/people/morris|publisher=University of Maryland|accessdate=16 April 2014}}</ref><ref name=SenBook>{{Citation | last = Morris | first = Christopher | contribution = Contributors | editor-last = Morris | editor-first = Christopher | title = Amartya Sen | pages = xi - xii | publisher = Cambridge University Press | location = Cambridge New York | year = 2009 | isbn = 9780521618069 }}</ref>

His main research areas are [[Ethics|moral]], [[Ethics|legal]] and [[political philosophy]] as well as [[Practical reason|practical rationality]].<ref name=Cambridge>{{Cite journal | last = Table of contents | title = Contributors, Christopher W. Morris | journal = Social Philosophy and Policy | volume = 29 | issue = 1 | pages = xvii-xix | publisher = Cambridge Journals | doi = 10.1017/S0265052511000021 | date = January 2012 | url = https://dx.doi.org/10.1017/S0265052511000021 | ref = harv | postscript = .}}</ref>

== Early life ==
Morris gained his psychology and philosophy degree from [[Vassar College]], [[Poughkeepsie (town), New York|Poughkeepsie, New York]] in 1971, he went on to [[University of Toronto]] to do both his philosophy master's (1974) and his philosophy doctorate (1977).<ref name=CV />

== Academic career ==
From 1977 to 1982 he was the assistant professor of philosophy at the [[University of Ottawa]]. Morris then spent a number of years as a visiting lecturer at a number of universities. In 1986 he took up a position as associate professor of philosophy at [[Bowling Green State University|Bowling Green State University (BGSU)]], he was made senior research fellow of BGSU's Social Philosophy & Policy Center in 1990, and from 1994 until he left in 2001 to go to the [[University of Maryland]], he was their professor of philosophy.<ref name=CV />

