'''Egil Anders Wyller''' (born 24 April 1925) is a Norwegian philosopher, historian, non-fiction writer and translator. He was born in [[Stavanger]], the son of [[Trygve Christian Wyller]] and Anne Kathrine Dons, and brother of [[Thomas Christian Wyller]]. He was assigned professor at the [[University of Oslo]] from 1969. Among his books are ''Tidsproblemet hos Olaf Bull'' from 1958 and ''Enhet og annethet'' from 1981. He has translated dialogues of [[Plato]] into [[Norwegian language]], and been a co-editor of the book series ''[[Idé og tanke]]''. He was decorated Knight, First Class of the [[Order of St. Olav]] in 2000.<ref name=snl>{{cite encyclopedia|title=Egil Anders Wyller |encyclopedia=[[Store norske leksikon]] |editor-last=Godal | editor-first=Anne Marit | editor-link=Anne Marit Godal |publisher=Norsk nettleksikon |location=Oslo |url=http://www.snl.no/Egil_Anders_Wyller |language=Norwegian |accessdate=9 March 2012}}</ref><ref name=nbl>{{cite encyclopedia|year=|title=Egil A Wyller |encyclopedia=[[Norsk biografisk leksikon]]|first=Tore |last=Frost |editor=[[Knut Helle|Helle, Knut]] |publisher=Kunnskapsforlaget|location=Oslo |url=http://www.snl.no/.nbl_biografi/Egil_A_Wyller/utdypning |language=Norwegian|accessdate=9 March 2012 }}</ref>

